'''Constantin Dăscălescu''' ({{IPA-ro|konstanˈtin dəskəˈlesku|}}; 2 July 1923 &ndash; 15 May 2003) was a Romanian [[communist]] politician who served as [[Prime Minister of Romania]] (21 May 1982 &ndash; 22 December 1989) during the communist rule of [[Nicolae Ceauşescu|Nicolae Ceaușescu]] until the [[Romanian Revolution]].

In 1991, after the revolution, he was sentenced to life in prison. After five years he was released on medical grounds.

