==Etymology==
Among [[Latter Day Saints|LDS]] [[linguistics|linguists]], prevalent consensus of the reading of the name "Sariah" is שׂריה ''Śaryāh'' ("princess of [[Tetragrammaton|Jehovah]]"), and an alternative voicing of the name [[Seraiah]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Fronk|first=Camille|title=Desert Epiphany: Sariah and the Women in 1 Nephi|url=http://maxwellinstitute.byu.edu/publications/jbms/?vol=9&num=2&id=222|publisher=Neal A. Maxwell Institute for Religious Scholarship|accessdate=2012-09-28}}</ref>

==Book of Mormon Movie==
In ''[[The Book of Mormon Movie, Vol. 1: The Journey]]'', adapted from First and Second Nephi, Sariah was portrayed by [[Jan Broberg Felt]]. The portrayal was highly influenced by [[Arnold Friberg]] paintings of the characters.

