{{Infobox Chinese-language singer and actor <!------See WikiProject Chinese-language entertainment-------> | gender = female | image = | image_size = | caption = | name = Yang Rong |other names = |birth_name = |tradchinesename =楊蓉 |simpchinesename =杨蓉 |pinyinchinesename=Yáng Róng | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1981|06|03}} | birth_place = [[Baoshan, Yunnan|Baoshan]], [[Yunnan]], [[China]] | death_date = <!-- {{death date and age|}} --> | death_place = | death_cause = | residence = [[Beijing]], [[China]] | ethnicity = [[Bai people|Bai]] | nationality = | education = | alma_mater = [[Shanghai Theatre Academy]] | occupation = [[Actress]] | years_active = 1997–present | organization = | label = Yu Zheng Studio | spouse = <!-- {{marriage||}} --> | partner = | children = | parents = | relatives = | awards = <!-- {{Awards|award= |year= |title= }} --> | signature = | signature_alt = | signature_size = }}
'''Yang Rong''' ({{zh|s=杨蓉|t=|p=}}, born 3 June 1981) is a [[Chinese people|Chinese]] actress of [[Bai people|Bai]] origin. She is best known for her roles in ''Cosmetology High'' and ''[[Memory Lost]]''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Actress Yang Rong releases new photos|url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/photo/2014-05/06/c_133313761.htm|work=Xinhua News Agency|date=May 6, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=China, I love you|url=http://www.whatsonweibo.com/93-military-parade/|work=whatsonweibo.com|date=September 3, 2015}}</ref>
==Early life== Born in [[Baoshan, Yunnan|Baoshan]], [[Yunnan]], on June 3, 1981, Yang Rong graduated from [[Shanghai Theatre Academy]], where she majored in acting.
In 1992, at the age of 11, she enrolled at Yunnan Art School to study dance. Two years later, she studied acting in [[Shanghai Normal University]] Xie Jin School of film and Television Art.<ref>{{cite news|author= |url=http://www.dooland.com/magazine/article_239958.html |script-title=zh:我是需要细品的白葡萄酒——专访《宫锁珠帘》徐佳袭香扮演者杨蓉 |newspaper=dooland.com |date=October 19, 2012 |language= zh|location=}}</ref> In 1997, by age 16, she was accepted to [[Shanghai Theatre Academy]] and graduated in 2001.
==Career== Yang Rong made her acting debut in [[Xie Jin]]'s war epic film ''[[The Opium War (film)|The Opium War]]'', playing a servant girl. She gained attention in the early 2000s for her roles in ''Young Emperor'' (2001), ''The Censor of Qing Dynasty'' (2003) and ''Young Justice Bao 3'' (2005).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.sina.com.cn/o/2004-07-06/15533006422s.shtml|script-title=zh:从《少年天子》到《大清御史》|date=July 6, 2004|website=Sina|language=zh}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://yule.sohu.com/20070521/n250134982.shtml|script-title=zh:小风筝不食人间烟火 包青天3杨蓉流露真挚情意|website=Sohu|date=May 21, 2007|language=zh}}</ref> In 2007, Yang was cast as [[Qing Wen]] in the drama ''[[Dream of the Red Chamber]]'', based on [[Cao Xueqin]]'s classical novel.<ref>{{cite news|author= |url=http://yule.sohu.com/20071006/n252491779.shtml |script-title=zh:舞台剧《红楼梦》演员与角色对照表 |newspaper=Sohu |date=January 6, 2007|language=zh |location=}}</ref> In 2008, she starred alongside [[Chen Kun]] and [[Liu Ye (actor)|Liu Ye]] in romantic drama ''Love Ensure This Life''.
Yang first worked with [[Yu Zheng]] in 2010, and appeared in her first comedy series ''Happy Mother-in-law, Pretty Daughter-in-law'' (2010).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.ifeng.com/zz/detail_2011_02/12/4630799_0.shtml|script-title=zh:杨蓉颠覆形象演憨傻角色|website=iFeng|language=zh|date=February 12, 2001}}</ref> Her performance received positive reviews and the following year, Yang was signed to Yu Zheng's studio.<ref name=yang /> She was then cast in ''[[Palace II|Palace 2]]'' (2012), the second installment of [[Yu Zheng]]'s ''Gong'' series wherein she played an antagonist.<ref>{{cite news|author= |url=http://yule.sohu.com/20120116/n332293314.shtml |script-title=zh:《宫锁珠帘》杨蓉出演反一号 性格刁钻独树一帜 |newspaper=Sohu |date= January 16, 2012|language=zh |location=}}</ref> In 2013, she played contrasting roles in two of Yu's productions; a cold and domineering concubine in historical television series ''[[Legend of Lu Zhen]]'' and an adorable and young lady in wuxia series ''[[Swordsman]]''.<ref>{{cite news|author= |url= http://ent.qq.com/a/20130528/015595.htm |script-title=zh:《陆贞传奇》演云恋悲情结局 杨蓉演技获赞 |newspaper=Tencent |date= May 28, 2013 |language=zh |location=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://yule.sohu.com/20130228/n367386171.shtml|script-title=zh:《笑傲江湖》湖南热播 小师妹杨蓉悲情收场|website=Sohu|date=February 28, 2013|language=zh}}</ref> Both series were popular and earned high ratings, leading to increased popularity for Yang. Known for portraying notable second leading roles, Yang impressed audiences with her performances in ''[[Palace 3: The Lost Daughter]]'' (2014), ''[[Love Yunge from the Desert]]'' (2015) and ''[[Lady & Liar]]'' (2015), at times even outshining the main leads.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hebei.news.163.com/14/0415/14/9PSL621K02790EO4.html|script-title=zh:《宫锁连城》杨蓉耍狠飙演技反派称能激发创作|website=NetEase|language=zh|date=April 15, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jstv.com/n/ws/jw/201502/t20150212_11920057.shtml|script-title=zh:《千金女贼》杨蓉接班雪姨演蛇蝎女|website=Jiangsu TV|language=zh|date=May 2, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author= |url=http://ent.163.com/13/0704/11/92UGNV6D00031GVS.html |script-title=zh:《云中歌》昨日杀青 杨蓉主动请缨演霍成君 |newspaper=NetEase |date=July 4, 2013 |language=zh |location=}}</ref>
After numerous secondary roles, Yang was finally cast by Yu Zheng in her first leading role, in the historical television drama ''Cosmetology High'' (2014). The series was one of the most watched dramas in China while it aired on [[Hunan Television]], and established Yang as a leading actress in her own right.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.ifeng.com/a/20141012/40327625_0.shtml|script-title=zh:杨蓉《美人制造》演萌蠢女主获赞 观众：萌萌哒表情要醉|website=iFeng|language=zh|date=October 12, 2014}}</ref><ref name=yang>{{cite web|url=http://yule.sohu.com/20141010/n404975169.shtml|script-title=zh:《美人制造》热播 细数杨蓉那些年与于正的缘分|website=Sohu|language=zh|date=October 10, 2014}}</ref> In 2016, Yang starred in crime drama ''[[Memory Lost]]'', adapted from Ding Mo's novel.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.163.com/16/1026/15/C4AJTJ3Q00038793.html|script-title=zh:杨蓉《美人为馅》玩悬疑 黑裙登场演绎性感警花|website=NetEase|language=zh|date=October 26, 2016}}</ref> The series was a hit in China and internationally, and raised Yang's popularity.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.163.com/16/1228/11/C9CCSA4Q00038FO9.html|script-title=zh:《美人为馅》23亿播放量收官 杨蓉白宇CP感超强|work=[[NetEase]]|date=December 28, 2016}}</ref><ref name=couple>{{cite web|url=http://ent.163.com/16/1204/00/C7DD5NNV000380BQ.html#p=C7E8DIIJ00AJ0003?baike|script-title=zh:谢娜刘诗诗遭催生 黄轩帮挡驾自曝空窗四年|website=NetEase|date=December 4, 2016|language=zh}}</ref> This was followed by another leading role in the well-received police drama, ''K9 Coming''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.sina.com.cn/v/m/2017-03-17/doc-ifycnpiu8933705.shtml|title=《警犬来啦》杨蓉暂别古装换警装 贾景晖变犬爸|date=March 17, 2017|work=Sina|language=zh}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.163.com/18/0129/11/D9AIVLP4000380EN.html|title=《警犬来啦》安徽卫视开播 青春励志引领寒假档|date=January 29, 2018|work=Netease|language=zh}}</ref>
